-- Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, Candente, Minsur, Rio Cristal
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-01-26T19:07:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-26/peru-stocks-buenaventura-candente-minsur-rio-cristal.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 1:23 p.m. Lima time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose for a fourth day, gaining 1.2
percent to 21,678.90. The  MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD)  climbed 1.7
percent to 2,800.99.  Mining stocks gained after metals advanced in  New York  and
 London , said  Jorge Ramirez , a trader at Lima-based brokerage
Coril SAB.  Rio Cristal Resources Corp. (RCZ)  , a Canadian
exploration company, rose 8.3 percent to 13 cents, a two-month
high.  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA  (BVN PE), the country’s
biggest precious-metals miner, gained for the third session in
four, adding 2.2 percent to $42.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), the
world’s fourth-largest tin producer, rose for a fourth day,
adding 3.2 percent to 2.94 soles.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian mining exploration company with operations in
Peru, advanced 1.9 percent to $1.05.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
